                    "articleID": [6981, 3661, 2661, 2006, 1761],
                    "name": "More about growth in the first 6 months - mild malnutrition",
                    "text": "Attention! Your child is losing weight (or not gaining weight) and has a low weight for their length/height. This situation could have happened in a course of few weeks, hence consider finding out some immediate causes: recent infectious disease or diarrhoea, some other chronic illness, insufficient and a very improper diet, changes in the immediate environment, etc. Be sure to schedule an examination with a health worker to discover the cause, correct the loss and continue to monitor the growth of your child. Your child needs to have an improved nutritious and balanced diet."
